<br>
You have all been a family to me and I will always have a part of me that misses you.  Why you ask??   Well, I believe that while everquest is a part of my life, Real life is what pays the bills.  There have been times when I WANTED to attend a raid, or FA camp but couldn't due to work schedule or other RL things.  I have been talking with a young wood elf named Jeanine who very much wanted to join our family.  She completed her adopt a newbie quest and met all the pre-reqisites for admision into the guild.  Unfortunatley, she had to work on the day of the FA camp.  Now she is told that fledglings can ONLY be tagged at FA camps.  I believe that a game (as fun and adicting as it may be) should not come before RL obligations, and that a person should not be punished for that.<br>
<br>
